The call

    conxFinder(storage.add(linArray.get(i).get(0)), linArray.remove(i), linArray.get(i).get(a), linFin);

doesn&#39;t work because:
* `storage.add(linArray.get(i).get(0))` returns a boolean, but the first parameter of `conxFinder` is an `ArrayList` (it must be `storage`)
* `linArray.remove(i)` returns a `ArrayList&lt;String&gt;` (the element at position `i`), but the second parameter of `conxFinder` is a `ArrayList&lt;ArrayList&lt;String&gt;&gt;` (it must be `linArray`)

You could try to work around those problems by writing helper methods:

    private static ArrayList&lt;String&gt; add(ArrayList&lt;String&gt; storage, String value) {
        storage.add(value);
        return storage;
    }

    private static ArrayList&lt;ArrayList&lt;String&gt;&gt; remove(ArrayList&lt;ArrayList&lt;String&gt;&gt; linArray, int i) {
        linArray.remove(i);
        return linArray;
    }

